@startuml Storage Enforcement Architecture
!theme default
left to right direction

title Storage Enforcement System - Architecture Overview\n(Dynamic Configuration-Driven)

package "API Layer" {
  component "File Upload\nEndpoint" as FileUpload
  component "Storage Status\nEndpoint" as StorageStatus
  component "Download\nEndpoint" as Download
}

package "Service Layer" {
  component "StorageEnforcementService" as Service {
    frame "Core Methods" {
      interface "get_enforcement_config()" as GetConfig
      interface "can_upload()" as CanUpload
      interface "can_download()" as CanDownload
      interface "get_status_display()" as GetStatus
      interface "should_send_warning()" as ShouldWarn
      interface "get_cleanup_urgency()" as GetUrgency
    }
  }
}

package "Data Access Layer" {
  component "StorageEnforcementConfigRepository" as Repo {
    frame "Repository Methods" {
      interface "find_by_organisation()" as FindOrg
      interface "find_system_default()" as FindDefault
      interface "get_config_for_organisation_or_default()" as GetOrgOrDefault
      interface "create/update/delete()" as CRUD
    }
  }

  component "StorageEnforcementConfigSeed" as Seed {
    frame "Initialization" {
      interface "seed_default_configs()" as SeedDefault
      interface "seed_organisation_config()" as SeedOrg
      interface "get_b2c_hard_enforcement()" as B2CHard
      interface "get_b2b_soft_enforcement()" as B2BSoft
    }
  }
}

package "Database" {
  database "storage_enforcement_configs" as DB {
    frame "Columns" {
      card "id, organisation_id" as DBKey
      card "enforcement_type (hard|soft|none)" as DBType
      card "warning_threshold_percent" as DBThreshold
      card "grace_period_days" as DBGrace
      card "warning_frequency (daily|weekly|once)" as DBFreq
      card "actions_json" as DBActions
    }
  }
}

FileUpload --> Service : calls
StorageStatus --> Service : calls
Download --> Service : calls

Service --> GetConfig : uses
Service --> CanUpload : uses
Service --> CanDownload : uses
Service --> GetStatus : uses
Service --> ShouldWarn : uses
Service --> GetUrgency : uses

Service --> Repo : queries

GetOrgOrDefault --> FindOrg : 1. Lookup\nby org_id
GetOrgOrDefault --> FindDefault : 2. Fallback\nto system default

Repo --> DB : reads/writes

Seed --> Repo : populates
Seed --> B2CHard : uses template
Seed --> B2BSoft : uses template

B2CHard --> DBActions : creates JSON
B2BSoft --> DBActions : creates JSON

note right of GetOrgOrDefault
  **Configuration Resolution:**
  1. Try organisation_id lookup
  2. Fall back to system default
  3. Never fail (internal defaults)
end note

note right of DBActions
  **JSON Flexibility:**
  {
    "0_to_50": { status, upload, download, notifications },
    "50_to_80": { ... },
    "80_to_100": { ... },
    "100_plus": { grace_period_days, ... },
    "grace_period_expired": { ... }
  }
end note

legend
|<#90EE90> **Dynamic Configuration** |
|  ✅ All enforcement rules in database |
|  ✅ Per-organisation overrides |
|  ✅ No hardcoded thresholds |
|  ✅ JSON actions for flexibility |
end legend

@enduml
